						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājarājakēsarivarman (Rājarāja I): Year 8 = 992-93 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is also fragmentary. </p>						

						<p>It records a gift of a lamp to be burnt in the temple of Tiruvāyppāḍi Śrī-Kṛishṇa ••••• Perumāḷ, by a certain <hi rend="italic">Maṉṟāḍi</hi> Tiruva ••••• di Kūttaṉ of Śrī Dantivarmamaṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">Brahmadēyam,</hi> on the northern bank <hi rend="italic">(vaḍakarai)</hi> (of the Kāvērī).</p>						

